3 objects with 3 methods:
model object:
	model: function:
		args: 0
		returns: undefined
		behaviour: has 2 variables. 1 which pulls the value of the input, another which pulls the div.
		declares both to global scope.
		Purpose: to take in the value of the input and get the html div.
view object:
	view: function:
		args: 0
		return: undefined
		behaviour: takes the global div variable and pushes the input into the html view.
		purpose: so the user sees the actual input in the div.
controller object:
	controller: function;
		args: 0
		return: undefined
		behaviour: takes in the model and view function, and executes respectively.
		purpose: to act as the function controller between the model and the view

